ğŸ” Technical Implementation
   Unlike methods that call external OS binaries (like subprocess.run('clear')), 
   this module uses ANSI Escape Sequences sent directly to the standard output. 
   This makes it faster and more lightweight.

* Sequence \033[2J: Clears the entire screen.
* Sequence \033[H: Moves the cursor to the home position (top-left).
* Buffer Flush: The module forces a sys.stdout.flush() to ensure the screen clears immediately, 
   even if the output is buffered.

